todo-list-python
📝 To-Do List (Python Project)
A simple and scalable To-Do List application built using Python with OOPS concept and functions.

Add new tasks with title, description, and due date View all tasks with their status Update task status (Pending / Completed) Delete tasks by ID Persistent storage using JSON file

Project Structure

todo_list_project/
│
├── main.py          # Entry point (CLI menu)
├── task.py          # Task class
├── task_manager.py  # TaskManager class (CRUD operations)
├── file_handler.py  # Load/Save tasks
└── tasks.json       # Stores all tasks
Example Usage

📌 To-Do List Menu
1. Add Task
2. View Tasks
3. Delete Task
4. Update Task Status
5. Exit
📜 License
This project is open source and available under the MIT License.

✅ Features Implemented:

Add, View, Update, Mark as Done, Delete, and Exit

Task limit: 8 tasks maximum

Task IDs auto-generated and updated after deletions

Simple console-based menu

Includes input validation and clear user message

▶️ How to Run

Put all three files in one folder (e.g., todo_app/).

Open a terminal or VS Code terminal in that folder.

Run:
